definition: apex/crown of the head/top/roof/most/to carry on the head/to push to the top/to go against/to replace/to substitute/to be subjected to (an aerial bombing, hailstorm etc)/(slang) to "bump" a forum thread to raise its profile/classifier for headwear, hats, veils etc

sentences.english: In addition, the number of the zenith delay parameters has effect on the tropospheric refraction.
sentences.chinese: 天顶延迟参数个数的选择对对流层折射有较大影响。

sentences.english: Photoelectric tracking system with horizontal gimbal can not track objects near zenith.
sentences.chinese: 天顶跟踪盲区是地平式光电跟踪系统的固有缺陷。

sentences.english: It was like the ceiling of Grand Central Terminal, but seemed even closer.
sentences.chinese: 天空很像中央火车站的天顶，只是好像离得更近。

sentences.english: But he clasped both his hands over his breast, and cast his eyes towards the zenith.
sentences.chinese: 但他紧握双手捂在胸前，抬眼眺望天顶。

sentences.english: An unvaried pall of cloud muffled the whole expanse of sky from zenith to horizon.
sentences.chinese: 一望无际的云幕蒙住了从天顶到地乎线的整个夜空。

sentences.english: Tropospheric Zenith Delay Prediction Accuracy for High-Precision GPS Positioning and Navigation.
sentences.chinese: 高精度GPS定位与导航的对流层天顶延迟预报精度。

sentences.english: An unwearied pall of cloud muffled the whole expanse of sky from zenith to horizon.
sentences.chinese: 一望无际的云幕蒙住了从天顶到地平线的整个夜空。

sentences.english: Once, the Invid and the Zentraedi savaged this entire part of the galaxy, fighting their war.
sentences.chinese: 从前，因维人和天顶星人的战火曾经蔓延了整个星系。

sentences.english: Wind from the compass points, sun at meridian.
sentences.chinese: 那自四面到临的风，天顶的太阳。

definition: the twelve equatorial constellations or signs of the zodiac in Western astronomy and astrology, namely: Aries 白羊[Bai2 yang2], Taurus 金牛[Jin4 niu2], Gemini 雙子|双子[Shuang1 zi3], Cancer 巨蟹[Ju4 xie4], Leo 獅子|狮子[Shi1 zi3], Virgo 室女[Shi4 nu:3], Libra 天秤[Tian1 cheng4], Scorpio 天蠍|天蝎[Tian1 xie1], Sagittarius 人馬|人马[Ren2 ma3], Capricorn 摩羯[Mo2 jie2], Aquarius 寶瓶|宝瓶[Bao3 ping2], Pisces 雙魚|双鱼[Shuang1 yu2]
constellation (arch., now 星座)/one of the 28 constellations of traditional Chinese astronomy and astrology/motion of stars since one's birth (predetermining one's fate in astrology)
